---

<Layout title="Airline Luggage Limits: kg to lbs Quick Guide" description="Convert airline luggage weight limits from kg to lbs. Know exactly how much you can pack with our quick reference for common airline baggage allowances." keywords="luggage weight, kg to lbs luggage, airline baggage limit, carry on weight, checked bag weight, baggage allowance conversion, suitcase weight">
  <div class="max-w-3xl">
    <article class="prose dark:prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose">
        <a href="/blog" class="hover:text-amber-600">Blog</a> <span class="mx-1">›</span> <span class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">Weight</span>
      </nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-2">Airline Luggage Limits: kg to lbs Quick Guide</h1>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-8">June 9, 2025 • 4 min read</p>

      <p>Nothing ruins the start of a holiday like being told your suitcase is overweight at check-in. Most airlines display weight limits in kilograms, but if you are used to thinking in pounds, that number might not mean much. Here is a quick guide to help you pack smart.</p>

      <h2>Common Airline Weight Limits Converted</h2>
      <p>Most airlines use these standard limits:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Carry-on bag:</strong> 7 kg = 15.4 lbs</li>
        <li><strong>Carry-on bag (generous):</strong> 10 kg = 22 lbs</li>
        <li><strong>Checked bag (economy):</strong> 20 kg = 44 lbs</li>
        <li><strong>Checked bag (standard):</strong> 23 kg = 50.7 lbs</li>
        <li><strong>Checked bag (business):</strong> 32 kg = 70.5 lbs</li>
        <li><strong>US domestic (legacy carriers):</strong> 50 lbs = 22.7 kg</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>The Quick Conversion</h2>
      <div class="bg-amber-50 dark:bg-amber-900/20 border border-amber-200 dark:border-amber-800 rounded-xl p-5 my-6 not-prose">
        <p class="text-center text-lg font-mono font-bold text-amber-700 dark:text-amber-400">kg × 2.2 = lbs | lbs ÷ 2.2 = kg</p>
      </div>
      <p>For a rough estimate, just double the kg number and add a bit. A 23 kg limit is approximately 50 lbs. A 7 kg carry-on limit is about 15 lbs.</p>

      <h2>Tips to Avoid Overweight Fees</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Buy a luggage scale</strong> — portable digital scales cost under $15 and save you from surprise fees of $50-200</li>
        <li><strong>Weigh before you leave</strong> — check your bag at home, not at the airport</li>
        <li><strong>Account for souvenirs</strong> — leave 2-3 kg of headroom for your return trip</li>
        <li><strong>Wear heavy items</strong> — boots and coats on the plane do not count toward luggage weight</li>
        <li><strong>Distribute weight</strong> — if travelling with a partner, balance bags to keep both under the limit</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Overweight Bag Fees by Airline Type</h2>
      <p>Exceeding your luggage allowance can be expensive:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Budget carriers</strong> (Ryanair, Spirit): $30-75 per kg over the limit</li>
        <li><strong>Full-service carriers</strong> (BA, Delta): $50-200 flat fee for overweight bags</li>
        <li><strong>Long-haul flights:</strong> fees tend to be higher, sometimes $100+ per bag</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Empty Suitcase Weights to Consider</h2>
      <p>Remember that your suitcase itself has weight:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Lightweight carry-on: 1.5-2.5 kg (3.3-5.5 lbs)</li>
        <li>Standard checked bag: 3-5 kg (6.6-11 lbs)</li>
        <li>Hard-shell large case: 4-6 kg (8.8-13.2 lbs)</li>
      </ul>
      <p>If your airline limit is 23 kg and your suitcase weighs 4 kg, you only have 19 kg (42 lbs) of actual packing space.</p>

      <div class="border-t border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-800 mt-10 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Try It Now</h3>
        <a href="/convert/weight" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-amber-500 text-white text-sm font-semibold hover:bg-amber-600 transition-colors">Open Weight Converter →</a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</Layout>
